text: Robert Fitzgerald Diggs (born July 5, 1969RZA at Allmusic) is an American rapper and producer, as well as a member of the hip-hop group Wu-Tang Clan, better known by his stage name, RZA. He was a member of Gravediggaz. He was known as Rzarector. This is a pun on 'resurrector'. RZA has written two books. RZA started his music career in 1991 when he released the EP Ooh I Love You Rakeem. == Discography == * Bobby Digital in Stereo (1998) * Digital Bullet (2001) * Birth of a Prince (2003) * Digi Snacks (2008) == References == Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:Rappers from New York (state) Category:Musicians from New York City
